        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Not every AI platform cost can be traced to a single team or feature. Guardrail services, model routing infrastructure, embedding generation pipelines, shared vector stores, and usage monitoring systems serve multiple consumers simultaneously. These costs accumulate in a shared pool that must be distributed across consuming teams through explicit rules. Without clear shared cost pool policies, these overheads either disappear into a central AI budget (opaque to teams) or are allocated arbitrarily — undermining the integrity of the entire cost allocation programme."
          }
        ]
