          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The three splitting methods"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Even split"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The pool total is divided equally among all registered consumers. This is the simplest approach and requires no usage telemetry beyond knowing how many teams consume the service. It is fair when usage is roughly uniform but becomes inequitable when one team consumes an order of magnitude more than another."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from decimal import Decimal\nfrom typing import List, Dict\n\ndef even_split(pool_cost: Decimal, consumers: List[str]) -> Dict[str, Decimal]:\n    if not consumers:\n        return {}\n    share = (pool_cost / Decimal(len(consumers))).quantize(Decimal(\"0.01\"))\n    # Assign remainder to first consumer to avoid rounding loss\n    remainder = pool_cost - share * Decimal(len(consumers))\n    result = {c: share for c in consumers}\n    result[consumers[0]] += remainder\n    return result\n\n# Example: monitoring cost $1,200 shared by 4 teams\nprint(even_split(Decimal(\"1200.00\"), [\"payments\", \"risk\", \"cx\", \"fraud\"]))\n# {'payments': Decimal('300.00'), 'risk': Decimal('300.00'), ...}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token-proportional split"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each team's share equals the pool cost multiplied by the fraction of total tokens (or requests) they contributed during the period. This requires per-call telemetry that captures which consumer triggered the shared service call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from decimal import Decimal\nfrom typing import Dict\n\ndef proportional_split(\n    pool_cost: Decimal,\n    usage_counts: Dict[str, int],  # team -> token count or request count\n) -> Dict[str, Decimal]:\n    total = sum(usage_counts.values())\n    if total == 0:\n        return even_split(pool_cost, list(usage_counts.keys()))\n    shares = {\n        team: (pool_cost * Decimal(count) / Decimal(total)).quantize(Decimal(\"0.01\"))\n        for team, count in usage_counts.items()\n    }\n    # Correct rounding error\n    rounding_error = pool_cost - sum(shares.values())\n    first_team = next(iter(shares))\n    shares[first_team] += rounding_error\n    return shares\n\n# Example: guardrail cost $800, usage split:\nprint(proportional_split(\n    Decimal(\"800.00\"),\n    {\"payments\": 60000, \"risk\": 25000, \"cx\": 15000},\n))\n# payments: $480.00 (60%), risk: $200.00 (25%), cx: $120.00 (15%)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fixed-weight split"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Weights are agreed in advance (typically at the start of each quarter or fiscal year) based on expected usage, team size, or revenue contribution. No per-period telemetry is needed: the weights are stored in a config file and applied at billing close."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# shared-pool-weights-2026-Q3.yaml\npolicy_version: \"2026-Q3\"\neffective_from: \"2026-07-01\"\neffective_to: \"2026-09-30\"\nreview_trigger: \"Usage share of any team changes by > 15 percentage points\"\n\npools:\n  platform_engineering:\n    split: fixed\n    weights:\n      payments:  0.40\n      risk-eng:  0.30\n      cx-ops:    0.20\n      fraud:     0.10\n\n  guardrails:\n    split: proportional\n    metric: guardrail_api_calls  # sourced from platform telemetry\n\n  model_routing:\n    split: even\n    consumers: [payments, risk-eng, cx-ops, fraud, compliance]"
          }
        ]
      },
